            <bug_when>2008-08-05 16:51:47 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>The widget now has a &quot;shadow&quot; property, which takes a &quot;Decorator&quot; as argument. If set an additional Element is added to the container element, which overlaps the container. It is most useful for top level widgets like menus or windows, where the parent widget does not clip the shadow.

Modern menus, tooltips and windows already use shadows.


